we are in front of a spa.  there isn't too much activity other than some kids doing backflips in front of us (at the OTTAWA sign).  we are in front of the Parliament, probably 700m away. a little ahead, there is a traffic light so many slowed down and were quiet.

Not too many cars going by as well as pedestrians, although there were 3 pedestrians communicating behind the decibel device . Loading truck beside us that is making a lot of noises that spiked the decibel reader by 5dB twice in the second take. There is a quiet alleyway as well as we are further away from Sussex road .

column30: we are in front of a pub, but there is no business in it as it is broad daylight.  on the other side of the road there is a doctor office.  between these mentioned buildings there is a parking lot which is almost fully packed.  in the second attempt, there was a dog barking which contributed to the loudness. about 100m away from us in front, we can see some construction happening.

column20:
Location 1: William/York.
Lots of restaurants, caf√©s and small markets. Also hotels Courtyard Marriott and Andaz very close. Near the parliament (major tourist site). Weather is better, very sunny and warmer now.
Medium traffic flow. Definitely not packed but decent amounts of people walking by, especially in and out of shops and diners.

Location 2: York/Byward Market
Young people, few middle aged. No kids. Behind a parking site so not many active services near. More small shops and markets. Still close to main area and Parliament. Narrower sidewalk, more corner area.
column30: Definitely busier time of day, peak lunch hour. Market and dining areas busy. Older building, some look revitalized. Very catered to tourists in terms of services available. Lots of space to walk including crosswalks. Very safe with traffic lights and signs everywhere
Near an alleyway and not to much traffic resulting in lower reading. More pedestrian than cars

Not a lot of cars or pedestrians in this part of the street, as well as no busy roads as and we are getting further away from Sussex . One of the resteraunts was playing music towards the street. Parked cars were around the area in front of the decibel reader. Additionally, there was an air conditioner unit near us that made a lot of noise.

column30: very little traffic

we are directly in behind a truck whose engine is very loud.  behind us is an empty stalls for seeking hotdogs but no one is there. there is still a packed parking lot in between our road and the one across from us. there are few cars that passed us but there have been many pedestrians who contributed to the time.
very little traffic, in front of parking garage

There was more roads with intersections such as the intersection between Clarence and byward (near by ward market ). A lot more cars in the area as well as one truck. A lot more pedestrians in the area due to the fact a lot of them are near the market.  Parking parage nearby where cars are going into.
Both maxes may be high because a truck was leaving/arriving when they occurred. Min readings had a lot less activity, mostly just noise from people talking.

we are in the middle of a very pedestrian area. there are buildings surrounding us from all sides except for behind us, specifically restaurants, but it is too early for people to stop by them so they continue to drive.  there are many chatting pedestrians but they are not too close and thus are not the reason for high volume. the second time around, there was a massive truck which led to the very high volume.

We were under a market with a lot of cars and one truck that went by. Lots of pedestrians walking into the markets and in the area as well as music consistently playing from the market. A intersections between byward and Clarence street.

we are on a very narrow sidewalk with many pedestrians which is what contributed to the noise levels. there are many markets behind and in front of us so there is a narrow parking lot running the length of the street (narrow was in one car space). this parking lot seems to block out the noise of cars and almost acts like a noise barrier/buffer. people on the opposite side are tunic to parallel park which leads to a bit more noise
